<div class="box en">💡 <strong>Bottom line:</strong> Crypto companies that listed over the past year trade far below their debut prices: Gemini -89% ($37→$4.19), BitGo -77% ($22.43 debut), Bullish -71% ($90 open). With Grayscale, Payward (Kraken), Consensys and Ledger delaying their IPOs, 2026 has seen just one completed crypto IPO (down ~70%). Crypto company valuations are leveraged proxies on volumes and prices, so as spot volume fell to its lowest since November 2023, fee revenue and equity multiples compressed together. The open question is whether this drawdown is cyclical beta or a structural re-rating of pure-play crypto intermediaries. Sources: INN, CoinDesk.</div>
